# Provide links or keys to any relevant tickets, articles or other resources
# Footer format: Token: value  or  Token #value
# Example: Jira issue: ABC-123
# Example: BREAKING CHANGE: removes /api/login endpoint

# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be
#    feat     (new feature for users)
#    fix      (bug fix for users)
#    docs     (documentation changes)
#    style    (formatting, whitespace; no code change)
#    refactor (code restructuring; no behavior change)
#    perf     (performance improvements)
#    test     (adding or updating tests)
#    build    (build system or external dependencies)
#    ci       (CI configuration files and scripts)
#    chore    (tooling, maintenance; no production code change)
#    revert   (reverts a previous commit)
# --------------------
# Remember to
#    Use the imperative mood in the subject line
#    Do not end the subject line with a period
#    Separate subject from body with a blank line
#    Use the body to explain what and why vs. how
#    Can use multiple lines with "-" for bullet points in body
#    Use ! after type/scope for breaking changes: feat!: ...
#    Or use BREAKING CHANGE: footer (must be uppercase)
